# Add a Route Skill (TanStack Router file-based)

This project uses **TanStack Router file-based routing** under `src/routes/`. The route tree is generated into `src/routeTree.gen.ts` by `@tanstack/router-plugin` (wired through `tanstackStart()` in `vite.config.ts`).

## 1. Decide the file name

Map the URL to a file under `src/routes/`:

| URL | File |
|---|---|
| `/` | `src/routes/index.tsx` |
| `/about` | `src/routes/about.tsx` → imports from `src/pages/about/` |
| `/posts` | `src/routes/posts.tsx` |
| `/posts/$postId` | `src/routes/posts.$postId.tsx` |
| pathless layout wrapping `/dashboard/*` | `src/routes/_dashboard.tsx` (+ children: `_dashboard.index.tsx`, `_dashboard.users.tsx`, …) |
| route group folder | `src/routes/(auth)/login.tsx`, `src/routes/(auth)/sign-up.tsx` (parentheses make a non-URL group) |

The dot separator is the path separator. The `$` prefix marks a dynamic param. The `_` prefix marks a pathless segment.

## 2. Minimum route file

```tsx
import { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'

export const Route = createFileRoute('/posts')({
  component: PostsPage,
})

function PostsPage() {
  return <div className="p-8">Posts</div>
}
```

Rules:

- Always **named export** `Route`. No default export on a route file.
- The string passed to `createFileRoute('/posts')` MUST match the file path; the router plugin enforces this.
- Component name is PascalCase; UI lives in `src/pages/<feature>/` — route files stay thin (loader, guards, `pendingComponent`).

## 3. Add params and search

```tsx
import { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'
import { z } from 'zod'

const searchSchema = z.object({
  page: z.number().int().positive().catch(1),
  q: z.string().optional(),
})

export const Route = createFileRoute('/posts')({
  validateSearch: (search) => searchSchema.parse(search),
  component: PostsPage,
})

function PostsPage() {
  const { page, q } = Route.useSearch()
  return <div className="p-8">page={page}, q={q ?? ''}</div>
}
```

For dynamic params (`/posts/$postId`):

```tsx
const { postId } = Route.useParams()
```

## 4. Add a loader

Prefer TanStack Query in loaders when data should be cached:

```tsx
import { productDetailQueryOptions } from '#/lib/query/product'
import { authStore } from '#/stores/auth.store'
import { LoadingFallback } from '#/components/loading-fallback'

export const Route = createFileRoute('/product/$slug')({
  loader: async ({ params, context, abortController }) => {
    const accessToken = authStore.state.accessToken
    const product = await context.queryClient.fetchQuery(
      productDetailQueryOptions(accessToken, params.slug),
    )
    return { product }
  },
  pendingComponent: () => <LoadingFallback variant="page" label="Loading…" />,
  component: ProductPage,
})
```

Direct API calls are fine for one-off fetches that don't need caching:

```tsx
loader: async ({ abortController }) => {
  const data = await getCurrentUser(accessToken, abortController.signal)
  return { user: data }
}
```

- Pass `abortController.signal` to API functions for cancellation.
- Use `loaderDeps` when the loader must re-run on search-param changes.
- The loader's return type is inferred — `useLoaderData()` is fully typed.
- For expected `ApiError` failures, return an error field; re-throw unexpected errors.

## 5. Server functions for mutations / server-only fetches

```tsx
import { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'
import { z } from 'zod'

const inputSchema = z.object({ title: z.string().min(1).max(200), body: z.string() })

export const createPost = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })
  .validator(inputSchema.parse)
  .handler(async ({ data }) => {
    // run server-only code (DB, secrets, headers)
    return { id: 'generated-id', ...data }
  })
```

Call from a component or loader: `await createPost({ data: { title, body } })`.

## 6. Linking and navigating

- Use the typed `<Link to="/posts/$postId" params={{ postId }}>…</Link>` — never retype path strings.
- Programmatic navigation: `const navigate = useNavigate(); navigate({ to: '/posts/$postId', params: { postId } })`.
- Update search params: `navigate({ search: (s) => ({ ...s, page: 2 }) })`.

## 7. Verify

- Save the file. The router plugin re-generates `src/routeTree.gen.ts` on the next dev/build cycle. Don't edit that file.
- Run `yarn tsc --noEmit` — typed search/params/loaders are checked end to end.
- Run `yarn lint`.

## Acceptance checklist

- [ ] File path matches the URL via TanStack file-based conventions.
- [ ] `createFileRoute('<exact path>')` matches the file location.
- [ ] No default export.
- [ ] Search params (if any) validated through Zod via `validateSearch`.
- [ ] Loader passes `signal` to `fetch`; returns typed data.
- [ ] Pending and error UI declared when the route can be slow / fail.
- [ ] Internal navigation via the typed `<Link>` / `useNavigate()` API — no hardcoded path strings outside the `to:` prop.
- [ ] `src/routeTree.gen.ts` not hand-edited.
